description:
I went last night for the first time after having this restaurant hyped up to me and was a bit disappointed.

What I liked: 
the clam chowder was good;
the garlic bread was OK (I prefer it crispier);
the bread pudding was excellent;
the seafood in my cioppino was fresh.

What I didn't like:
I don't know if they were having a bad night in the kitchen or if it's always liked this but the tomato broth had zero flavor. I had to add salt, but it just didn't have any flavor. It tasted like they opened a can of stewed tomatoes, heated them up and then tossed in the seafood at the end;
the cracked crab also had no salt, it was just butter and garlic and didn't taste good until I added the salt myself;
the shortbread cookie in the strawberry shortcake was bitter, I don't know if it's supposed to be that way or if they messed it up but it wasn't good.

Customer service:
It was terrible, the waitress never came to our table to check on us. We had to flag down a different waitress on two separate occassions after trying to make eye contact and flag our waitress down while she went to ALL the other tables except for ours. It was strange how the waitress purposely avoided our table considering that we weren't difficult customers, didn't complain about anything or ask for anything out of the ordinary. We flagged the waitress down to order another cup of soup and to ask if our crab was going to be enough so that we could order the full one if not. She just was not interested in our table at all. I can't see myself going back.
